Program: Free Thinking
Title: 18th-Century Crime and Punishment
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b040hysp
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 17 Apr 2014
Philip Dodd explores eighteenth-century attitudes to the law, crime and punishment. Norman S Poser, Emeritus Professor at Brooklyn Law School, is the author of Lord Mansfield: Justice in the Age of Reason. Antonia Hodgson's first novel is called The Devil in the Marshalsea. Dr Lucy Powell is a former BBC Radio 3 and AHRC New Generation Thinker. Geoffrey Robertson QC is a civil liberties barrister and author. Producer: Harry Parker. Show less